(INNOVATIVE MEDICAL SOLUTIONS INC.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Quality Manual) Tj
0 -20 Td
(QM-RM-002: Risk Management for Medical Devices) Tj
0 -40 Td
(Document ID: QM-RM-002) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Revision: 1.5) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Effective Date: February 5, 2024) Tj
0 -40 Td
(1. PURPOSE AND SCOPE) Tj
0 -20 Td
(This Quality Manual section establishes the risk) Tj
0 -20 Td
(management process for medical devices in accordance) Tj
0 -20 Td
(with ISO 14971:2019 and FDA guidance documents.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(2. RISK MANAGEMENT PROCESS) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2.1 Risk Analysis) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Risk analysis shall be conducted systematically to:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Identify intended use and reasonably foreseeable misuse) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Identify hazards and hazardous situations) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Estimate risk for each hazardous situation) Tj
0 -40 Td
(2.2 Risk Evaluation) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk acceptability criteria shall be established) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risks shall be evaluated against acceptance criteria) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk-benefit analysis shall be performed where applicable) Tj
0 -40 Td
(2.3 Risk Control) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Risk control measures shall be implemented in order:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(1) Inherent safety by design) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2) Protective measures in the device or manufacturing) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3) Information for safety including warnings and) Tj
0 -20 Td
(   precautions in labeling) Tj
0 -40 Td
(2.4 Residual Risk Assessment) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Residual risk shall be evaluated after risk control) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Overall residual risk shall be acceptable) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Benefits shall outweigh residual risks) Tj
0 -40 Td
(3. RISK MANAGEMENT FILE) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3.1 Risk management file shall contain:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk management plan) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Hazard analysis and risk assessment) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk evaluation criteria) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk control measures and verification) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Residual risk analysis) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk-benefit analysis) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk management report) Tj
0 -40 Td
(4. POST-MARKET SURVEILLANCE) Tj
0 -20 Td
(4.1 Information Collection) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Post-market information shall be actively collected:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Customer complaints and adverse event reports) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Post-market clinical follow-up data) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Literature and regulatory announcements) Tj
0 -40 Td
(4.2 Risk Management Review) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Post-market information shall be reviewed regularly) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk assessment shall be updated if necessary) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Additional risk control measures shall be implemented) Tj
0 -20 Td
(  if new risks are identified) Tj
0 -40 Td
(5. COMPETENCE AND TRAINING) Tj
0 -20 Td
(5.1 Personnel involved in risk management shall be:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Competent based on education, training, and experience) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Trained on risk management procedures and tools) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Familiar with applicable standards and regulations) Tj
0 -40 Td
(6. MANAGEMENT RESPONSIBILITY) Tj
0 -20 Td
(6.1 Top management shall ensure:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk management policy is established) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Adequate resources are provided) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Risk management is integrated with quality system) Tj
